<div id=3D"outline-container-org55deb9c" class=3D"outline-3">
<h3 id=3D"org55deb9c">Fran=C3=A7ois Pottier announced</h3>
<div class=3D"outline-text-3" id=3D"text-org55deb9c">
<p>
We are pleased to announce a new release of <a href=3D"https://gitlab.inria=
.fr/fpottier/sek">Sek</a>, a library that offers efficient ephemeral (mutab=
le) and persistent (immutable) <i>sequence</i> data structures, plus effici=
ent conversions between these two forms.
</p>

<p>
This new release introduces optimizations that speed up several operations,=
 including random access (<code>get</code>, <code>set</code>), splitting, a=
nd concatenation. For details, please see the <a href=3D"https://gitlab.inr=
ia.fr/fpottier/sek/-/blob/master/CHANGES.md?ref_type=3Dheads">change log</a=
>.
</p>

<pre class=3D"example" id=3D"orgfd071c9">
opam update &amp;&amp; opam install sek
</pre>

<p>
Happy hacking,
Arthur Chargu=C3=A9raud &amp; Fran=C3=A7ois Pottier.
</p>
